                  </hi>. I am the wife of John Tester. On the 20th of Oct., a few minutes before ten o'clock, I was going by the Observatory, on Wool<lb></lb>wich Common—I had a basket, containing a handkerchief and 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., which I left at the gate, in the prisoner's care—I came back in about an hour and a half, and all the soldiers were gone—I saw my basket, but the handkerchief and 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. were gone—I am sure it was in it when I gave it to him.</p>
